	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Considering something like 90% of the wealth and income in the western world is held/made by about 2% of the population, you can't tell me the wealthy paying 78% of the tax burden is their "fair share." The remaining 98% or so of the population only hold about 10% of the wealth and make 10% of the income split between them, but pay 22% of the taxes. You call this fair?<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />
So you are saying that the top 2% should pay 90% of the taxes.  That is just insane.  Of course it would end up bankrupting the U.S. if it did occur.  The loss of revenue from such a policy would be staggering.  The government is MUCH less effecient with money, so the loss of that much money from the economy would frankly cause a depression the likes of which we haven't seen since the 30's.<br />
 <br />
How about we just make it so that everyone makes the same amount.  That would be fair wouldn't it?  Everyone is cut a paycheck by the government for the work they do.  I wonder if that has been tried before?  :/</p>
	
	
	
