	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Slythe</b><br /><i>You make a completely subjective judgement that the wealthy pay more than their 'fair share' yet don't seem to either understand or agree that the very fact that our current system allows some people to make so excessively much in the first place, tens of millions of dollars a year , might not be 'fair'.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />
It absolutely is fair.  They made that money in most cases, by being very good at what they do, and taking big risks that need to be rewarded.  Someone comes up with a brilliant idea, starts a company, makes a fortune.  Someone else is smart enough to realize that it is a brilliant idea, risks their savings to invest in said company, and makes a fortune.  Said bright idea is made possible by this investment and has a positive impact on society.<br />
 <br />
There are always exceptions...someone got lucky with the roll of the dice, won the lottery, commited a crime and didn't get caught, ect...but those are exceptions and more uncommon then some try to imply.<br />
 <br />
Hey, i'm far from rich...but i'm not so short sighted that I can't see that a tax cut for those well above me, has a positive impact on my life.</p>
	
	
	
