	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>AegnorCuthalion</b><br /><i>So you are saying that the top 2% should pay 90% of the taxes. That is just insane. </i><hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />
The top 2% contol 90% of the money. <br />
 <br />
If a family makes a modest income... say $50,000 a year they likely spend $40,000 just on living expenses. Suppose they pay 20% in taxes $10,000, a bit low for their tax bracket. That eats 100% of their disposable income! <br />
 <br />
Now imagine a family who makes $2 million a year. Their expenses are pretty well covered with $500,000, and a 40% tax on them (not unheard of in that bracket, with all the write offs, shelters, and expensive tax attorneys) leaves them with 10 times more <i>disposable</i> income than the other family makes total! <br />
 <br />
 <br />
Who isn't covering their share of the tax burden?</p>
	
	
	
