	<p>I've said it before, i'll say it again:<br />
<br />
You only need so much money before no luxury is beyond your means, as Taamar pointed out using numbers.<br />
<br />
Vital necessities cost the same no matter how much money you make (barring any special assistance, but then that's just deferring the cost). My Dad's 3000$ in medical expenses every month would cost the same as anyone else needing the same medical treatment, only he isn't rich, so it definitely makes a hard impact on him.<br />
<br />
The lower tax bracket may pay much much less, but they also need all of the money they have in order to scrape by.</p>
	
	
	
