	<p>Something that apparently you and I will always disagree on, Taly, is the availability or non-availability of methods of wealth accumulation that not only are not "evil," but work through the process of helping others in a completely win-win type situation. Such opportunities are readily available. Most people don't take advantage of them because either they are comfortable in the economic rut they've been living in for 20 years and they don't want to be uncomfortable for the relatively short amount of time it would take to bust their butts and do something about it or they have pea-sized dreams for what they want to have and/or accomplish in the future.<br />
 <br />
That's about all I have to say on the subject. I should have left the office two hours ago.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Tevyn Eagleye<br />
51st Pathfinder of Solusek Ro<br />
Retired</div>
	
	
