</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>The chief problem is that 'making' money really more typically entails tricking someone out of their money.<br />
 <br />
The only commodity that truly exists is time. If I make you work incredibly hard for four hours to compensate me for one hour of my time, I have cheated you out of three hours of your life.<br />
 <br />
And the reasons for this all stem from the facts that Adam Smith chose to ignore: mobility of capital and labor are extremely imperfect. There can never exist "perfect competition" in a captialist system because even when I'm charging scandalous prices for my services, it will take competitors so long to acquire the capital and labor to start up their operations and provide the same services as I do that I will already have an excess of wealth by the time they do. And wealth, once you have it, is much harder to lose than it is to gain.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15562" target="_blank">Hunter Yzen Danek<br />
</a>Forest Stalker<br />
Order of the Jade Dragon<br />
Xegony</div>
	
	
